text:
DOC: don't download NYU in examples

Use ADHD instead. The rational is to have less different data sources, in
order to have less stress on the download when building the docs.

DOC: make sym-links in examples directories

Fixes #1124

Have "make html" create symbolic links to examples/nilearn_cache from all
the example subfolders nilearn_cache directory (on unix systems only, of
course). The goal being to federate the cache across all examples, in
order to minimize computation.

DOC: rewrite the parcellating section

The goal of this rewrite is to move all the code sample to the
notebook-like example, and keep only a high-level discussion in the
narrative documentation.

Indeed, modifications of the code in the examples (as in the previous
commit) cause code-rot in the narrative documentation that is very
hard to control.
DOC: link from example to narrative docs
